title: ASIN | Snowflake Documentation
paragraphs: Computes the inverse sine (arc sine) of its argument; the result is a number in the interval [-pi/2, pi/2].

This expression should evaluate to a real number greater than or equal
to -1.0 and less than or equal to +1.0.
The data type of the return value is FLOAT.
Returns the arc sine in radians (not degrees) in the range [-pi/2, pi/2].
